# External Code Protocol
## Before taking ANYTHING from outside this project
1. Check license: MIT/Apache=safe | GPL=careful | no license=ask first
2. Log in docs/SOURCES.md: URL + what was taken + why + license
3. Strip to minimum — no dead code, no unused imports
4. Understand every line you copy (no blind paste)
5. Run tests after integrating
## Search GitHub FIRST for: auth, CRUD, API clients, parsers, scrapers
## NEVER copy
- Code you cannot explain line by line
- Code with no tests and no documentation
- Anything with >5 open critical issues
